			<div class="description col six">
				<br />
				<p><a href="../">EmoTweet</a></p>
				<p><em>2008</em></p>
				<p><em class="background">&ndash; Affective analysis and visualization of tweets.</em></p>
				<br />
				<p>EmoTweet sources live tweets, senses emotions and creatively visualizes them. A combination of six basic emotions- happiness, anger, fear, surprise, sadness, and disgust at various scales make up a final visualization of the tweet Textual emotion recognition is based on the lexicon of emotion-related words, where each word is associated with a vector of weights for each emotion type and by several simple heuristics (usage of upper cases, exclamation mark, emoticons etc.).</p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><b>role:</b> Conceptualization, Software Development, Visualizations.</p>

<p><b>skills:</b> Processing, Synesketch API, Twitter API.</p>

